30/04/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The government adopted and forwarded to parliament on Friday (28 April) draft amendments to the penal code, introducing tougher sentences against pedophiles, drug dealers and racketeers. 
The new provisions would impose between three and 12 years of imprisonment for pedophiliac crimes and over 20 years for especially grave ones. 
Convicted drug dealers would be jailed for between three and 15 years, while racketeers who use violence to collect funds owed would serve between three and ten years. 
(HINA - 28/04/06)
